<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">New spells on Test!</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=563437" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
Geoff writes:
<blockquote><font color="beige">
According to those who are good at parsing the spell definitions file(s), there's a LOT of changes coming to spells...
<P>
For example, the level for various rezz spells has been lowered drastically for both paladins and clerics, with clerics now getting their first rezz at 14.
<P>
So far, druid, cleric, wizard, paladin, and enchanter spells have been confirmed as changed on Test. This author is unaware of changes to spells for the other classes - but would NOT be surprised to see them.</font></blockquote>
If you want details on these changes to spells on the Test Server, head on over to Caster's Realm to Baelish's <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=4159" target="_blank">article on the topic</a>. 
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=563437">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
			  </td>
		</tr>

		</table>

	</td>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
