			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Everyone thats complaining about class balancing, needs to take a step back.  You say that this will make it unfair to other classes, think about this: Why did they make the change in the first change?  It because of class balancing! They are constantly working on class balancing, this is not the first time somthing along the lines have happened.  The game is constantly evolving.  Think about how much money this game makes, then think about whether they want to keep people happy or not.  I'm sure they have people that sit around in a room and discuss what could be done to make the game better, and class balancing is one of them i'm sure!  Now, the only way that they would probably ever listen to people's comments is if there was a giant outcry for one class to get better abilities.  And it would have to come from not only people who play said class, but others who can just see it from gameplay.  Point being, everyone's turn will come for class balancing so just be paitent.  And like a few others have noticed, the rez changes make gameplay better for everyone, in fact in my opinion better for the people grouping with pally's and cleric and not themselves!<BR>
<BR>
Sorry for the extremely long post, but think about it, verant knows what they're doing, and there is more to come...<BR>
<BR>
Sidilos (notice i didn't complain about rogues) Soulstabber<BR>
Rogue of Brell
